  "text": "At 11:46 PM, during a brownout in my grandmother’s house, my cousin Carlo sat straight up in bed and whispered: “Mom… there’s someone underneath.” His mother thought he meant under the bed. So she got a candle, knelt down, and looked. There was nothing there. Just dust. One missing slipper. And a trail of wet soil leading from Carlo’s bed to the wall. The strange part was, nobody had gone outside. But at the bottom of the wall, right beside Carlo’s bed, someone had written three tiny words in mud: “He didn’t ask.” That afternoon, Carlo had been playing behind the house with the other kids. There was an old santol tree there. Under it was a small mound of dirt that everyone avoided, although no one ever explained why. When the ball rolled beside it, the younger kids froze. Carlo laughed. He said, 'It’s just dirt.' Then he picked up the ball. Nobody saw what happened next clearly. One cousin said Carlo stepped on the mound. Another said he kicked something. But everyone agreed on one thing. Right after Carlo touched it, the rain stopped for exactly ten seconds. And from under the santol tree, they heard an old man cough. That night, Carlo developed a fever. His right foot turned red and swollen. His grandmother didn’t ask what happened. She just looked at his foot, then at the muddy writing on the wall, and said: “Why did you bring him inside?” No one slept after that. Because every few minutes, something would tap from inside the wall. Three soft taps. Then a pause. Then Carlo’s voice would answer, even though Carlo was asleep: “I’m here.” Near sunrise, his mother finally found the missing slipper. It was inside Carlo’s pillowcase. Filled with black soil. And tucked inside it was a tiny piece of paper, folded three times. His grandmother opened it, read it once, and started crying. Carlo’s mother asked what it said. But his grandmother only shook her head and whispered: “He isn’t the one they’re looking for.” That was when the crib began to rock.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "startSeconds": 0,
      "endSeconds": 8.04,
      "text": "At 11:46 PM, during a brownout in my grandmother’s house, my cousin Carlo sat straight up in bed and whispered:"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 8.04,
      "endSeconds": 10.74,
      "text": "“Mom… there’s someone underneath.”"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 10.74,
      "endSeconds": 13.34,
      "text": "His mother thought he meant under the bed."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 13.34,
      "endSeconds": 16.9,
      "text": "So she got a candle, knelt down, and looked."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 16.9,
      "endSeconds": 19.42,
      "text": "There was nothing there."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 19.42,
      "endSeconds": 26.62,
      "text": "Just dust. One missing slipper. And a trail of wet soil leading from Carlo’s bed to the wall."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 26.62,
      "endSeconds": 30.98,
      "text": "The strange part was, nobody had gone outside."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 30.98,
      "endSeconds": 38.22,
      "text": "But at the bottom of the wall, right beside Carlo’s bed, someone had written three tiny words in mud:"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 38.22,
      "endSeconds": 40.66,
      "text": "“He didn’t ask.”"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 40.66,
      "endSeconds": 45.54,
      "text": "That afternoon, Carlo had been playing behind the house with the other kids."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 45.54,
      "endSeconds": 48.14,
      "text": "There was an old santol tree there."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 48.14,
      "endSeconds": 54.56,
      "text": "Under it was a small mound of dirt that everyone avoided, although no one ever explained why."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 54.56,
      "endSeconds": 57.88,
      "text": "When the ball rolled beside it, the younger kids froze."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 57.88,
      "endSeconds": 59.56,
      "text": "Carlo laughed."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 59.56,
      "endSeconds": 61.48,
      "text": "He said, 'It’s just dirt.'"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 61.48,
      "endSeconds": 63.28,
      "text": "Then he picked up the ball."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 63.28,
      "endSeconds": 65.72,
      "text": "Nobody saw what happened next clearly."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 65.72,
      "endSeconds": 68.56,
      "text": "One cousin said Carlo stepped on the mound."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 68.56,
      "endSeconds": 71.7,
      "text": "Another said he kicked something."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 71.7,
      "endSeconds": 73.9,
      "text": "But everyone agreed on one thing."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 73.9,
      "endSeconds": 79.06,
      "text": "Right after Carlo touched it, the rain stopped for exactly ten seconds."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 79.06,
      "endSeconds": 83.18,
      "text": "And from under the santol tree, they heard an old man cough."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 83.18,
      "endSeconds": 87.38,
      "text": "That night, Carlo developed a fever."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 87.38,
      "endSeconds": 90.18,
      "text": "His right foot turned red and swollen."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 90.18,
      "endSeconds": 93.66,
      "text": "His grandmother didn’t ask what happened."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 93.66,
      "endSeconds": 99.08,
      "text": "She just looked at his foot, then at the muddy writing on the wall, and said:"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 99.08,
      "endSeconds": 102.68,
      "text": "“Why did you bring him inside?”"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 102.68,
      "endSeconds": 105.36,
      "text": "No one slept after that."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 105.36,
      "endSeconds": 110.04,
      "text": "Because every few minutes, something would tap from inside the wall."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 110.04,
      "endSeconds": 113.04,
      "text": "Three soft taps."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 113.04,
      "endSeconds": 115.28,
      "text": "Then a pause."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 115.28,
      "endSeconds": 119.68,
      "text": "Then Carlo’s voice would answer, even though Carlo was asleep:"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 119.68,
      "endSeconds": 121.72,
      "text": "“I’m here.”"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 121.72,
      "endSeconds": 126.2,
      "text": "Near sunrise, his mother finally found the missing slipper."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 126.2,
      "endSeconds": 128.56,
      "text": "It was inside Carlo’s pillowcase."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 128.56,
      "endSeconds": 131.24,
      "text": "Filled with black soil."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 131.24,
      "endSeconds": 136.68,
      "text": "And tucked inside it was a tiny piece of paper, folded three times."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 136.68,
      "endSeconds": 140.2,
      "text": "His grandmother opened it, read it once, and started crying."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 140.2,
      "endSeconds": 142.86,
      "text": "Carlo’s mother asked what it said."
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 142.86,
      "endSeconds": 146.94,
      "text": "But his grandmother only shook her head and whispered:"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 146.94,
      "endSeconds": 150.3,
      "text": "“He isn’t the one they’re looking for.”"
    },
    {
      "startSeconds": 150.3,
      "endSeconds": 154.34,
      "text": "That was when the crib began to rock."
    }
  ],
